value.0: The ghostly figure of an older man walks slowly on, his face haunted by the memories of his past.

Value.value: No, wait, not me... not here!
Please, no! I didn't finish, I need to go back! I need more time!

value.0: The ghosly outline of this small boy holds his arms wrapped tightly about himself, knuckles white with fear.

Value.value: I wanna wake up, I'm scared!

value.0: The ghostly image of a young girl plods slowly along as she looks around with fear in her eyes.

Value.value: I'm scared mommy, please help me!

value.0: A ghosly vision of a chisled man walks ever on  his face marked with anguish and dismay.

Value.value: This can't be! They have no one left!

value.0: Unseeing eyes dart back and forth as the ghostly image of this woman marches on.

Value.value: I can't see you, where are you? Why is it so cold?

value.0: The ghostly outline of this elf walks along slowly, her shoulder slumped in resignation.
An attractive, yet simple garment for those who merely wish to get about their day and not fuss too much with clothing.

A fine stringed instrument, a lute is very mobile, and as such, a favorite of traveling minstrels everywhere.  It has a pleasing sound, as the strings musical vibrations echo in the hollow wooden chamber and reverberate.

Value.value: In the end it's come to this ...  ?
Forgive me, I did not know...

value.0: The ghostly image of this older man trudges on with his head hung low.

Value.value: Who will be there for them now?

You have died.

Your soul has been drawn to the fugue plane where other souls wander the mostly flat gray expanse until they are gathered by their patron deities or make their way to the City of Judgment.

Should your soul return to the living it would have no memory of the time it spent in the fugue plane. 

You will also not have any memory of some period of time leading up to your death. How much time? That varies and is left up to each player to determine on their own. What we do know is that the moment of death is so traumatic that the mind simply cannot retain it in memory. Some may remember the last person with whom they spoke or what they were doing mere seconds before death, while others may not remember what happened over the last few days or even weeks before death. Although you will be unable to recall the exact details of what happened on your own, your memory of events shortly before death may give you clues and even suggest who you might seek out to determine what happened.

Upon your soul's reunification with your body you may experience different sensations. Some awaken with a severe headache lasting a day or two; others find that they suffer from a weakness of the body that can only be cured with ample bed rest. Some may even experience temporary amnesia and do not recognize anyone around them or places that are normally familiar. Others find that in the moment of battle the amount of adrenaline in their system combined with healing magic spurs them to action for a short while before they succumb to weakness and need rest. Still others may develop an abnormal fear of death or other phobias, neuroses or psychological aberrations.  What exactly will you feel? We leave this up to each individual to determine on their own, but you should bear in mind that death is traumatic to the body, the mind and the soul and returning from the dark place beyond death is at the very least disorienting and not without consequences. We are all affected by what happens to us, and you are encouraged to make your experience part of your role play.

May you find peace with your god when all things end.
